Personal transformation can be a challenging journey, but it is also one of the most rewarding experiences a person can have. The process of going from feeling stuck and unhappy with life to feeling fulfilled and excited about the future is a powerful one. I realized that I was living a life that was not in alignment with my true self. I was feeling unfulfilled and stuck in a job that paid the bills but left me feeling empty. I knew that I was capable of bigger and better things, but I didn't know how to make the changes that I needed to make. I felt trapped in my old self, and couldn't see a way out. I realized that no one was going to change my life for me. I had to take back control of my life, and start putting myself first. So, I made a decision to take action. I started working out and eating right, and began listening to personal growth podcasts. I started stepping outside of my comfort zone and working with a coach to help me with my mindset. Through this process, a new version of myself began to emerge. I found a career that truly lit me up, and I woke up each day excited for life. Now, as a coach, I get to help others find the same joy for life that I did. If you are feeling stuck and unhappy with your life, I encourage you to take action and start making the changes that you need to make. Remember that you are the only one who can change your life, and you have the power to create a better version of yourself. You deserve to live a fulfilling and joyful life, and you are capable of making it happen.  And if you want help along the way, I want to help you. Drop a 🔥 below to learn more.

Did you know there was a time that…

🫤I couldn’t leave my house alone
🙁wouldn’t make eye contact with strangers 
😬couldn’t call and make my own appointments 
😵wouldn’t socialize unless I’d been drinking 
🫣was always the most negative person in the room 
😢couldn’t imagine going on the way that I was 

My self-esteem was zero, happiness non-existent, and joy no where to be found. 

I was sad and considered myself damaged and broken. In addition, I didn’t think there was anything I could do about it. 

This photo proves otherwise. By the grace of GUS (God, Universe, Source) my path changed. I learned tools to change my thoughts, my reality, and ultimately my circumstances. So much so that I walked on this stage on Nashville Tennessee and performed something I wrote in front of 25,000 people without blinking an eye. 

I found my joy, my confidence, and my purpose. 

The purpose? Coaching…sharing with others how they could do the same.

The way my life shifted back then was freaking priceless. It was a gift from a higher power that I couldn’t ignore or deny. 

Now, I get to help people who were feeling how I felt every single day. I get to help them see that they can change their circumstances and show them how. I help them find their confidence, joy, and purpose. 

It’s such a gift 🙏

If you are currently more like the old version of me and you want to change that, I can help. 

I work with people one on one as well as in group settings. I also have a confidence Bootcamp coming up in March. If you’re interested in learning more and ready to get into the drivers seat of your life, drop a 🙋🏻 below. I would love to help you make that happen.

Everyone deserves a high quality of life. YOU deserve that.

As I stood on the top of a catamaran in the middle of the ocean in Costa Rica surrounded by dolphins, volcanos, and 12 of the most amazing people I have ever met, I couldn’t help but think…” this is only the beginning”.
I’m still coming down off the high of our trip to Costa Rica. I really didn’t have any expectations since this was our first trip, but if I did, my expectations were blown away. When I first started Club Lilles the goal was to connect people from all over the world who were looking for friendship, but not just any friendships. The goal was to connect people who wanted to play at a higher level energetically, spiritually, physically, and mentally. It was to connect people who wanted more than surface conversation…people who wanted to be in the company of others who were working on themselves and vibrating at a higher level.
We 1000% did that with this trip.
People from all over came together for one of the most amazing travel experiences I’ve ever been a part of. We learned about each other, learned about the Costa Rican culture, and experienced some pretty cool shit together. We ziplined through the jungle with monkeys, made empanadas with the locals, and became experts in coffee (don’t get Starbucks or DD).
This trip was just the beginning, and what a beginning it was!

Imagine waking up every morning feeling fulfilled, excited, and truly alive. The feeling of going from feeling stuck and unhappy with your life to feeling empowered and motivated to create a life that aligns with your true self is truly remarkable.

I know this firsthand because I've been there. I was living a life that didn't fulfill me and left me feeling empty, but I made a choice to take control and transform myself.

The process wasn't easy, but it was worth it. I found myself waking up every morning with purpose, passion, and joy. I discovered a career that I loved, and I found myself excited to face each day.

Now, I have made it my mission to help others experience the same transformation.

If you're feeling stuck or unfulfilled, it's time to take action. You are the only one who has the power to change your life, and I encourage you to take the first step towards a fulfilling and joyful life.

It may not be easy, but it will be worth it. Trust me; you are capable of creating the life you desire.

And if you want support along the way, I am here to help. As a life coach, it's my passion and purpose to help people find joy and fulfillment in their lives.

So if you're ready to take action and make a change, give me a 🔥 below. You deserve to live a life that brings you joy, and I'm excited to help you create it.

I used to share my heart here often. It has been a while since I have done that. May is mental health awareness month, and I felt inspired. I used to think I could never show when I was off my game. I felt like I needed to always hold it together for others, never show signs of "weakness" - of emotion - but that would mean I am not human. That would mean I am showing an unrealistic example of how we work through our challenges. As a coach, that would be doing a huge disservice to the people who trust me. The truth is, if you are not going through a challenging time at the moment, there is one coming eventually. Challenges are a given in this life. There will always be something around the corner that will shake up your world, mess it up, and force you to F it up and figure it out. What I mean by that is to embrace it, feel it, and move through it. It is okay not to be okay. It is okay to be working through something. It is normal, and anyone who tells you otherwise is full of 💩. Trust that you are not alone, and that whatever you are going through, you will get through it. If you need support, ask for it. If not from friends, there are professionals who will support you. As someone who has struggled with mental health over the years, I see you. This month, I am going to be showing up with more posts on this topic because it is essential to know that we are not alone, and it will get better. It gets better. I see you. You are loved. 💜

Imposter syndrome? Have you felt it? You’re not alone. 82% of people have felt like an imposter in their lives. So what can we do about it?

I hadn't felt like myself for months…

I thought that once I had my surgery and got rid of the problem, I would immediately go back to my old self. 👀 That wasn't the case.

The past six months have been a challenge. I hadn't realized that surgery was just the beginning. There's a lot that happens physically and mentally after having a major surgery like I did. Physically, I was frustrated because I didn't feel like myself. Parts of me were missing, scars were present, and getting back into shape, which used to take just a week of focus, was now much more challenging. It felt like I was putting in ten times the work with zero results. It was affecting all aspects of my being. I didn't want to take photos of myself, I didn't want to look in the mirror, and I wondered if I could ever go back to my old self.

I don't know if our old selves ever truly come back, and honestly, at this point, I wouldn't want it to. I have changed, I’ve grown, and adapted. Although there's no going back, I am excited for where I'm headed. Initially, I was hesitant to show my scars because I still feel a little self-conscious about them. However, after speaking with a client yesterday who is going through a similar situation, I find it important to share.

Life can throw unexpected challenges our way, especially when they're out of our control and impact our bodies and overall well-being. It's disheartening, but when has life ever followed a straight path? I have always faced challenges with tenacity. This one was no different. It may have knocked me down a few times, but it certainly didn't defeat me. Now, I am embracing my scars, and after six months, I am back on track physically.

“Oh shit, wtf is that?”

That was my first thought when I looked down at my stomach and saw a baseball-sized lump sticking out. At first, I thought I ate something weird, but when it kept showing up, I knew it was something more. With time I found out that I had a benign tumor in my uterus that was the size of a mango. Although it was great news that it wasn’t more serious, the reality of the situation hit me hard. I would have to have surgery to remove not only the tumor but my entire uterus…

Why was that an issue? I had a plan my entire life. My plan was to have kids of my own and a family. I could no longer do that in the way that I had been dreaming of. I had a choice at that moment…to sulk, cry, and focus on what I was losing, OR, to pivot, adapt, and embrace a new vision of my future. After a week or so of mourning the loss of what I thought my life would be, I was ready to pivot and move forward. 

Now I am 7 months post-surgery and feeling physically amazing. I am excited for my future and ready for what’s to come.

Life is like that…things rarely turn out the way we plan. In those moments, we have a choice to either let it knock us down or to use it as fuel to adapt and thrive. Obstacles are a given, it’s what we do with them that determines our outcome. 

Have you ever been hit with an obstacle or roadblock and wondered how to shift so that it could work for you? 

Do you want to know the hack that I use to get myself through anything that life throws my way? If so, drop the phrase “Success Loop” below!

You got to jump, you have to take a chance! 

There was a time when I would stand at the edge of the cliff of my dreams and just stare. I would think about jumping all day long yet when the time came, I would stand in fear. The older I got, the quicker life passed me by, and the more I realized I had a choice. Jump or stand there forever. 

Every successful person in this world has jumped. I knew, eventually I was going to have to jump. I did not want to be someone who just existed in this life…I wanted to be someone who LIVED. 

If you are waking up each day thinking that there has to be more to this life than it is, believe that it is. I beleived that…

The thing is, to get to that life, we have to jump. I couldn’t stand at the edge of what could be any more…I had to jump. We all have a gift in this life, something that we are meant for. Society tells us that a “gift” has to be running, jumping, singing, dancing…it’s more than that. 

When you are standing on the cliff of your life, and you see people soaring by…a friend who is kicking ass in a new business venture, or the neighbor who just bought their dream car…have you ever thought that maybe these people have identified their gift and are living their gift? 

The only way for YOU to soar is if you jump. Take the gift that is packed on your back, leap, pull the chord, and soar through the sky. At first, your chute won’t open right away. You will meet some resistance. You will hit roadblocks, your clothes will get all tattered and shit, cuts and bruises…but eventually your parachute will open. Sure, you can play it safe and deal without the cuts and bruises. You can stand on that cliff of life forever safe…but if you don’t jump, that parachute will never open and you will never know how you could have soared. 

Are you standing on the edge of your life with the urge to jump and soar? Comment JUMP below.

There we were, on a boat in the middle of the ocean in Costa Rica, dolphins jumping out of the water around us, and she turned to me and said, "I had plans set to take my life. That's when I saw your group coaching program. I decided I'd try one last thing and signed up". 

Clearly, she didn't follow through with her plan. Thank freaking GUS (God, Universe, Source). 

Ashley's story hits me deep in the feels because it reminds me of my own. She was ready to give up, but something inside of her whispered, "Not yet." Something outside of her led her to me. 

It has been a year since she decided to try "one last thing", and since that boat ride, she has been a participant in two more group coaching programs, has lost 43 pounds, and has gained confidence and self-love. Her children (btw she has 6 of them) think she's a total freaking badass, and she is...

Stories like Ashley's are the reason that I became a coach. I, too, at one point, wanted to end my life. I, too, had that tiny light within me that didn't let me go through with it. And when I lost several friends to suicide, I decided that I would dedicate my life to showing others that there are other options. I told myself that even if just one person lived because of what I shared, then it would all be worth it. 

It's worth it. 

Ashley is worth it...

I was worth it...

You are worth it.

I know that sometimes it can feel like the world is crashing down, like nothing will ever change. I have felt that too. It can change. Ashley and I are proof of that. 

Lucius Annaeus Seneca said, “Sometimes even to live is an act of courage.” This is true, and you are brave.

Picture this...

You’re 90 years old, sitting on your front porch rocking back and forth in a chair with your grandkids around you, telling them stories about your life. You have a big ass smile on your face, proud of the life you lived and grateful for everything you are blessed with. 

As you’re sharing stories,  you suddenly remember the time in your life when you had a choice. You were older but still young enough to shift the entire course of the life you were about to live. The choice was to continue to live unhappily and go through the motions of life OR to listen to that burning 🔥 desire in your gut. The one that keeps tugging at you, helping you to see that you were made for MORE...that you are CAPABLE of more. 

For a moment, you get a glimpse of how your life could have played out if you made the other choice and continued to play small. How it could have been if you never believed in yourself enough to do what you needed to do to make a dream your reality. The smile starts to diminish...and all of a sudden, your thoughts are interrupted by the loud laughter of the kids around you.

And then you put that huge ass smile back on your face and think:: Thank GUS 🙏 I Listened::

Are you living the way you want to live? Doing the things you want to do? Or have you been playing small out of fear?
What we focus on matters. I’m vibing high today. How are you vibrating? 👀 #punsfordays

It was the day that changed everything. 

I will never forget how my mom called, waking me up frantically on the phone.  I was 18 years old and had no idea the capacity of what was unfolding before my eyes. The part I could understand was that there were people who weren’t making it home. Mothers, sons, fathers, sisters, brothers, and friends all showed up to their daily lives with no idea that it would be their last. 

It’s always hard for me to understand hate, so I connected with the love. Focusing on the way everyone was helping one another, and in that moment of tragedy, we were all one. We may all be different, but we all feel the same emotions. In times of pain and hurt, it brings me comfort. We are human...together. 

There is evil in this world, and that was made very clear to me that day, but the good overpowers the evil...always. The light over the darkness. 

September 11th was the day I truly stepped into and understood what it meant to be an American. Watching the first responders do their jobs without a blink 🙏. Watching the people take care of one another despite their differences...taking each other in...loving one another, I will never forget it. 

I will never forget those who lost their lives that day, those who were affected...we can never forget what happened, and we can never forget how we responded 🙏 #neverforget

Is your brain just filling in the blanks based on the past? Or are you getting all the facts?

Masks…we all wear them at certain points. 

Sometimes just for a moment, sometimes more often than not. I used to think that if we were wearing a mask it meant that we weren’t truly being our authentic self and that wasn’t ideal. This morning while reading The Mastery of Self over on TikTok live, there was a paragraph that changed my perspective on this. It’s not the wearing of a mask that is bad. We often have to wear masks throughout our day to day (Think customer service voice while at work). The issue would lie in if we are wearing a mask to hide our true selves and ultimately using the mask as our “identity”, or if the mask we put on is, “with full awareness that it’s only a mask, a temporary identity to serve a function, and readily discards the mask when it is no longer needed.” 

When I started to dissect this thought I remembered my teaching days. I taught pre school kids. I definitely had to put a mask on when I walked into school each morning. That didn’t mean I wasn’t still my authentic self, it just meant I showed up as my authentic self without the swears etc. 

Do you wear masks throughout the day? What is a mask you have to put on a certain points in your life?

“The inner child is the gateway to discovering our True Self - to reconnecting with the Great Spirit.” -Robert Burney

What was something you absolutely LOVED as a kid? 

I definitely was fascinated by cars. I actually still love cars. When I go to the dealership, I often feel like I’m 5 years old again in a room full of power wheels. Or in my case, kit the car from Knight Rider. I love that feeling...the one where you feel like a kid again. 🚘

A lot of the work we do in our group coaching programs revolves around discovering, or I think it’s better put, RE-discovering our true selves. 

Who were we before the world told us who to be? Who were we before we cared what other people thought? 

Recently, I have been really intrigued by this idea and created a 12-week coaching program starting in January around re-discovering and connecting with the child that lives within each of us. I know the power of understanding ourselves on a deeper level, how that shows up in day-to-day life, and how we can use it to live a life filled with joy, love, and forgiveness. 

Are you interested in knowing your inner child? or think its all a bunch of 👀💩?

One of my favorite memories growing up was the Santa 🎅🏽 shag toilet seat cover my mom would pull out for the holidays.  There are certain things I see around the holidays that make my inner child smile. What’s your favorite memory from the holidays?

Taking care of business over here today! When I’m in a funk, I often let things go. My house gets messy, my fridge is empty, and I just feel blah. I could continue to sit in it OR I could get up and do something. What do you do?

Ain't that the truth 👀

They worked for us at one point. It was how we survived as kids. We put up walls, people pleased, were avoidant, or anxious. At the time, this was how we survived our worlds. The brain is cool like that, it always figures something out.

Here's the problem...

We are still using those coping methods even though we are now adults, and have the power to communicate and take care of ourselves.

Why? Because once the brain learns something, it will continue to do it unless we acknowledge and actively change it.

Imagine showing up to a situation empowered by knowing that you are capable, worthy, and have the tools instead of reverting to childhood coping methods.

This is one of the things we will cover in our 12-week upcoming group coaching program, Childhood Reclaimed: A Journey to Inner Freedom and for the next 10 people who join us, I am doing special one-on-one coaching with you.

I wanted to change that...

Are you interested in learning more about your inner child or do you want them to just shhh?

Growing up I used to watch that movie Big with Tom Hanks and think about how cool it would be if you could be an adult and a kid at the same time.

His downtown apartment with all the toys, having love, money and freedom, but also that childlike nature…seemed like a good idea, but knowing what I know about the world now, he would have been eaten by the wolves. 

I do think there’s a happy medium though. Sure, life may have hardened us, but that child always lives within us. Imagine being able to tap into them whenever you want. Imagine guiding them and being their mentor. Imagine being able to play and have fun in the best ways possible.
